ciscoSwitchStatsMIB.description: The MIB module provides management information for configuration and monitoring of traffic statistics on Cisco's switching devices.

csstConfigStatsOptionTable.name: csstConfigStatsOptionTable
csstConfigStatsOptionTable.description: This table contains a list of network traffic statistics options capable to be configured in csstConfigStatsMap for the statistics collection by the device.

csstConfigStatsOptionEntry.name: csstConfigStatsOptionEntry
csstConfigStatsOptionEntry.description: Each entry contains statistics information for a specific traffic statistics option.

csstConfigStatsOptionIndex.name: csstConfigStatsOptionIndex
csstConfigStatsOptionIndex.description: A unique value to indicate a specific traffic statistics option.

csstConfigStatsOptionDesc.name: csstConfigStatsOptionDesc
csstConfigStatsOptionDesc.description: Indicates the description corresponding to a specific traffic statistics option.

csstConfigStatsMapSize.name: csstConfigStatsMapSize
csstConfigStatsMapSize.description: Indicates the length of the csstConfigStatsMap object. This object value indicates the total number of traffic statistics options that can be configured in csstConfigStatsMap.

csstConfigStatsMap.name: csstConfigStatsMap
csstConfigStatsMap.description: Specifies the sequence of the traffic statistics options that are configured to be collected by the device. The length of this object is specified by the csstConfigStatsMapSize object value, and the value of each octet in the instance value of this object shall be unique and can only be selected from the set of csstConfigStatsOptionIndex values currently populated in csstConfigStatsOptionTable. If a traffic statistics option is configured in this object, the corresponding network traffic statistics will be collected on all the applicable interfaces in this device. Setting this object to a different value will trigger the csstConfigStatsIfTable to be repopulated.

csstConfigStatsIfTable.name: csstConfigStatsIfTable
csstConfigStatsIfTable.description: This table contains information about interface traffic statistics, which is configured through csstConfigStatsMap, for interfaces that are capable of providing such information. The total number of traffic statistics and the traffic statistics options populated in this table will be based on csstConfigStatsMapSize and csstConfigStatsMap. When the csstConfigStatsMap object value is changed to a different value, it will trigger this table to be repopulated.

csstConfigStatsIfEntry.name: csstConfigStatsIfEntry
csstConfigStatsIfEntry.description: Each entry provides traffic statistics information for a specific interface.

csstConfigStatsIfPackets1.name: csstConfigStatsIfPackets1
csstConfigStatsIfPackets1.description: The total number of packets counted on this interface for the traffic statistics option that is specified by the first octet value of the csstConfigStatsMap object.

csstSwitchStatsTable.name: csstSwitchStatsTable
csstSwitchStatsTable.description: This table provides specific L2/L3 traffic statistics information of switching engines.

csstSwitchStatsEntry.name: csstSwitchStatsEntry
csstSwitchStatsEntry.description: An entry providing L2/L3 traffic statistics information maintained by a particular switching engine entity (identified by entPhysicalIndex). An entry of this table is created if a switch engine with these L2/L3 traffic statistics is detected by the managed system. An entry of this table is deleted if the removal of the switching engine itself.
